<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870407-0120 </DOCNO><HL> Colorado NationalSays IRS ExaminationCould Reduce Profits</HL><DD> 04/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COLC TAXES </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Colorado National Bankshares Inc. said an Internal Revenue Service examination of the bank holding company's income tax returns could lead to &quot;future net income (being) reduced by approximately $13.2 million plus interest.&quot;    The company disclosed in the annual report that the IRS examined its returns for 1982 through 1984 and that a revenue agent proposed disallowance of certain deductions taken in those years in connection with the acquisition of several subsidiary banks.    &quot;It is anticipated that the company will receive shortly the assessment of tax based on that disallowance,&quot; Colorado National said in the annual report, adding that &quot;management intends to vigorously contest any disallowance.&quot;    A spokesman said the company hadn't yet received the assessment from the IRS. In 1986, Colorado National earned $2.2 million, or 21 cents a share, compared with 1985 earnings of $5.4 million, or 51 cents a share. </TEXT></DOC>